AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service.
This means you can run your code without creating or managing servers.

â¡ï¸ You upload your code to AWS, and AWS takes care of the rest â€” running, scaling, and stopping it.

ğŸ”¹ 2. How Does Lambda Work?
Hereâ€™s the basic idea:

You write some code (Python, Node.js, Java, etc.)
